# Feature Documentation Template

## Feature Name
<!-- Allowing Other devices besides Windows Machines ->

## Feature Type
_Core Feature

## Description
This feature allows anyone on any laptop/PC to access the application. I tested it for mac and windows(don’t have access to a linux machine). So linux integration still needs to be tested but doesn’t risk the others

## User Problem Solved
The problem that was solved was that the application was only limited to Windows users which isn’t the goal of the application. It is very important  that anyone on any system should be able to access the application. Not just the one that the majority of people have.
## How It Works
This feature works by checking the operating system of the user using the application on startup. This was already done; only windows were implemented prior. Then I added branches to the if statement to allow it to run. There were some syntax differences between OS’s. For example windows use backslashes while mac/linux use forward slashes to navigate files which was what was preventing mac systems from working. Also some things with the console are different between the systems so added checking there.

## Inputs
This just auto fires up when the program is launching no outside inputs required.

## Outputs
What the system produces (UI change, data output, API response).
The system actually loads for  Macs and Windows machines(linux still unknown)

## Dependencies
No needed dependencies just the side car card dependencies.

## Configuration / Setup
	During the setup for side car
Download the 2025 Windows Community Neo4j binaries at: https://neo4j.com/deployment-center/?gdb-selfmanaged&community
Download the JDK 25 compressed archive version of Java at: https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/#jdk25-windows
Unzip the binaries.
Move the contents of the binaries (i.e., the bin folder and all other folders and files) into OpenFinAL/open-fin-al/resources/neo4j-win and OpenFinAL/open-fin-al/resources/jre-win
With the binaries in place, you can move to the next step and start the application.
But for other systems make sure to download the respective ver+sions for your OS.
Then do jre-mac and neo4j-mac and for jre-linux and neo4j-linux


